Interface RunnableQueuture<V>

  • Type Parameters:
    V - The type of object being generated by the computation.
    All Superinterfaces:

    public interface RunnableQueuture<V>
extends Runnable, Queuture<V>
    A Queuture that can itself be executed as a Runnable. Running this object will result in this object's computation being executed in the current thread.
